Nearly one out of six NFL players will declare bankruptcy within 12 years of retiring from the league .
Despite earning millions of dollars - sometimes tens of millions - former players go broke at 1.1percent per year, the same rate as the rest of Americans .
Vince Young earned a reported $64million in salary and endorsement deals - but was bankrupt before he even finished his NFL career .
The average player makes $3.2million over the course of a career .